than those corresponding to 5 mg of rivaroxaban in an otherwise identical patient treated who is not concomitantly administered verapamil).  In other embodiments, the extended release formulation releases rivaroxaban at a rate such that the
pharmacokinetic profile of rivaroxaban is similar (e.g., bioequivalent) to that of an identical patient not treated with verapamil who is administered 2.5 mg rivaroxaban BID.
